underlying_goal: The user wanted to commit several documentation and configuration changes.
friction_detail: After pushing, the git status was momentarily confusing, but Claude quickly re-checked and confirmed the push was successful.
primary_success: Correctly separated unrelated changes into two logical commits with clear, distinct messages.
brief_summary: User initiated a commit of multiple changes. Claude correctly identified two separate logical changes, created a distinct commit for each, and pushed them to the remote repository after a brief moment of confusion with git status that it self-corrected.
